Kavitha wants to chat with Karthick

Most of us who have Internet connection also have a Wireless Modem (Router). By default all wireless routers will be in Master mode. Along with Master mode, we are adding adhoc mode to the router. Adhoc mode is used to connect with the nearby wireless devices that are also in adhoc mode.

We still retain master mode because not all devices support adhoc mode and so we don't want to leave out people. We can expand this way and invite our nieghbours to co-operate and form community wireless mesh network. This way people come together instead of being isolated inside their houses.
